just_use puzzle_from_snapshot.py

# label: TOOL (OPTIMIZE_PYTHON era)
# role: turn a captured snapshot into a puzzle session

Picks the Nth-slowest non-outlier snapshot from a JSONL
capture and posts it as a puzzle session. Hand + board
come straight from the captured state; layout uses
`geometry.find_open_loc`. Used to hand the agent's stuck
position to a human (Steve) for confirmation that the
agent's slow give-up was honest.

```
python3 puzzle_from_snapshot.py /tmp/perf_snapshots.jsonl
    [--rank N]   # 1 = slowest captured (default)
    [--label STR]
```

## Pointers

- Companion: `runaway_puzzles.py` — posts ONE puzzle per
  runaway projection, with JUST the evil card in hand.
- `agent_game.py --capture FILE` — produces the input.
